title: Source: Kupp to join Seahawks on 3-year deal
description: Wide receiver Cooper Kupp has reached agreement on a three-year, $45 million contract with the Seahawks, a source told ESPN's Adam Schefter on Friday.
author: Brady Henderson

title: Thomas ties TPC record after 16-shot turnaround
description: Despite a bogey on 18, Justin Thomas fired a jaw-dropping 62 that tied the TPC Sawgrass record (Tom Hoge, 2023) and gave him a whopping 16-shot improvement over Thursday's 78.
author: Paolo Uggetti

title: McIlroy in mix despite poor finish as Thomas makes historic comeback
description: Rory McIlroy is two off the halfway lead despite a disappointing finish to his second round at The Players, as Justin Thomas charged back into contention with a historic comeback.

title: Three share Sawgrass lead with McIlroy, Scheffler chasing
description: Rory McIlroy overcame an erratic display off the tee to get within a shot of the lead at The Players, as Scottie Scheffler made a strong start to his title defence.

title: I have to earn right to sing national anthem - Tuchel
description: England boss Thomas Tuchel says he must "earn the right" to sing the country's national anthem.

title: Inothewayurthinkin wins Cheltenham Gold Cup
description: Inothewayurthinkin wins the Cheltenham Gold Cup as Galopin Des Champs is denied a historic hat-trick.

title: Report: Tennessee Titans re-signing center Corey Levin
description: The Tennessee Titans have reportedly reached a deal to bring veteran center Corey Levin back into the fold 2025.

title: Rice, Queen help No. 11 Maryland rout No. 24 Illinois 88-65 in Big Ten quarterfinals
description: Rodney Rice scored 26 points, Derik Queen had 19 points and 10 rebounds and No. 11 Maryland routed No. 24 Illinois 88-65 on Friday night in the Big Ten Tournament quarterfinals. The Terrapins (25-7) will face the winner of the late quarterfinal between Michigan and Purdue in the semifinals. Jaâ€™Kobi Gillespie added 12 points and nine assists for Maryland.
author: MARK AMBROGI
